<p>I am trying to get Visual Studio 2015 (14.0) to use auto properties when implementing an interface using refactoring for C#.</p>  <p>I.e. I want this;</p>  <p><code>public object SomeProperty { get; set; }</code></p>  <p>as opposed to this;</p>  <p><code>public object SomeProperty {     get     {         throw new NotImplementedException();     }     set     {         throw new NotImplementedException();     } }</code></p>  <p>I have accomplished this in past versions of Visual Studio by editing the code snippet file (instructions <a href="http://codeimpossible.com/2010/11/29/Make-Implement-Interface-use-auto-properties/" rel="nofollow">here</a>) but I cannot get this to work using Visual Studio 2015. </p>